					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">STA address,X/Y</tt> always takes 5 cycles instead of 4 ... although X or Y has to be a known value so that you can know the resulting address at build-time .<br />They also cause an extra dummy read, from address+X or address+X-256, so can't be used safely to slow a write to $2007</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

